Subject: [PATCH] Fix checklist to match the real company template exactly
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Rebuilt against the actual source (Checklist_7_July_2026.pdf +
HDD_Checklist.et), byte-for-byte where it matters — the previous
version had silently paraphrased/corrected the wording instead of
reproducing it, which is exactly the bug being fixed here:

- All 21 Check Standard cells replaced with the exact source text,
  including original typos (maintanance, acitivty, inmediately),
  the mixed full-width/half-width parentheses in rows 3 and 11, the
  stray space-before-comma in row 10, the curly apostrophe in row
  12, and the embedded line break in row 6. Nothing 'corrected'.
- Acknowledge column: real form is two Yes/No checkboxes per row,
  not a 3-option dropdown — replaced the <select> (Yes/No/N/A) with
  paired radio buttons (Yes/No only). The fabricated N/A option
  doesn't exist on the real form.
- Auto-fill logic updated to match: hot-swap/no-FW-needed cases now
  get marked 'No' (matching how the real filled example does it,
  with the reason in Remarks) instead of a fabricated 'N/A'.
- Removed a top 'Engineer' field and a bottom 'Customer
  Acknowledgement' signature field — neither exists on the real
  form. Real form only has Signature + Date, at the bottom.
- Title fixed: 'Checklist for Engineer MA Service' (was reversed).
- Column header fixed: 'Acknowledge or not' (was abbreviated 'Ack').
- Remarks/notes section replaced with the exact source wording
  (was paraphrased), including the heading 'Remarks:' and note 3's
  original wording even though it references a 'no-operation' state
  that doesn't visually exist as a checkbox — that inconsistency is
  in the company's own document, preserved rather than silently
  fixed.
- Structure (No./Stage/Items rowspans, item groupings) was already
  correct and is unchanged — verified against source, not rebuilt.

Verified via Playwright screenshot against the source PDF layout,
plus a byte-level diff of every Check Standard cell against the
.et source using repr() to catch invisible punctuation differences.
All 30 existing tests still pass (pure front-end change).
